result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (3rd) and Operating w/ PAC (3rd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (3rd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (3rd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Dillon J. Gray was found guilty of OWI (3rd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • Dillon J. Gray was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.
Defendant is ordered to participate and successfully complete the Waushara County TAD/Safe Streets Program.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

records.addlTxt: 10:50 am case called. Defendant Dillon J. Gray in court with attorney Ryan T. Frank.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement reached and stated on record. Attorney Frank and defendant concur.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Arraignment held on Amended complaint, Attorney Frank confirms receipt, waives formal reading-plea entered. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea:  No Contest to Count 1. No Contest to Count 3. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses outright Count 2 and Dismisses and reads-in 15TR157, 15TR158, 15TR159 & 15TR160.  Court sentences the defendant to: COUNT 1-SWD and places on probation for a period of 2 years. CONDITIONS: COUNT 1 only- 45 day WCJ, with Huber and Good Time Credit. No objection to service of sentence in another jurisdiction. No credit for time served.  48 hour rule explained. TAD and successful completion. The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.  $1694.00 fine plus $42.50 blood draw costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. 24 mo DL revocation, 24 mo IID, OWI Assessment. AODA and follow through.  COUNT 3-SWD and places on probation for a period of 2 years. CONDITIONS: Same conditions as COUNT 1 -TAD and successful completion, AODA and follow through,   The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Appeal Rights Given.

NOT PUT OF RECORD: Attorney Ryan T. Frank in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Statment by Attorney Frank. Court directs defendant to contact Bobbie B for assessment and referral to TAD. Discussion between counsel and court.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for June 23, 2015 at 11:00 am.
